OL,3,CTaxpayer cost of Birmingham bin strike
OL,4,Crevealed
OL,6,FThe ongoing bin strike in Birmingham
OL,7,Fis estimated to have cost the city
OL,8,Fcouncil almost #4 million.
OL,10,FThe industrial action, which has been
OL,11,Fcausing disruption since January this
OL,12,Fyear, has left residents having to
OL,13,Fendure missed collections and heaps of
OL,14,Frubbish in the street.
OL,16,FBut it's also inflicted financial pain
OL,17,Fon the local authority, which
OL,18,Feffectively declared itself bankrupt
OL,19,Fin September 2023.
